"Rentalutions is perfect for a small, independent landlord such as myself.  I'm not sure how I would survive without it.  It keeps me organized, up to date, and on top of things with very little effort.  The added benefit of being able to list available apartments with ease over multiple platforms is reason enough to use it."








What does it cost to list my vacant rentals?


It's completely free. Whether you have just one unit or hundreds, it's completely free to post your listing and have it syndicated to our partner websites.





When does my listing get posted?


This depends on our partner sites. Most of them fetch our listings every 30 minutes or sooner. A few come by just once a day. You should see your listing go live on all sites within 24 hours though.





How do tenants contact me if they're interested?


Tenants can reply to your posting directly to you. You'll receive emails to the email address with which you created your Rentalutions account. If you provided a phone number, prospective tenants will be able to call you.





How do I know that my listing is being posted?


You should begin receiving tenant interest within 24 - 48 hours. If you do not, contact us and we can have our rental listing expert review your profile. No charge.




