POST APARTMENT HOMES

      
In this prospectus supplement and accompanying prospectus, we
refer to Post Apartment Homes, L.P. as Post Apartment
Homes and Post Properties, Inc. as Post
Properties. Unless the context requires otherwise, the
words we, us and our used in
this prospectus supplement and the accompanying prospectus refer
to Post Apartment Homes, Post Properties and their
subsidiaries.

      
We are one of the largest operators of upscale multifamily
communities in the United States. At March 31, 2005, we
owned 63 apartment communities containing approximately 24,523
apartment units, including 545 apartment units in two
communities held in unconsolidated entities and 205 apartment
units in one community currently under development. We are also
developing 145 for-sale condominium homes and are converting 382
apartment units in three communities (one in an unconsolidated
entity) into for-sale condominium homes through a taxable REIT
subsidiary. As of May 3, 2005, we had sold four apartment
communities containing approximately 1,102 apartment units that
were held for sale at March 31, 2005 and had entered into
an agreement to purchase an apartment community located in
Charlotte, North Carolina containing approximately 319 apartment
units. We also had two additional apartment communities
containing approximately 1,945 apartment units held for sale.
There can be no assurance that apartment communities under
contract to purchase or held for sale will close. At
March 31, 2005, approximately 51.9%, 17.4%, 8.6% and 8.1%
(on a unit basis) of our communities were located in the
Atlanta, Georgia, Dallas, Texas, Tampa, Florida and the greater
Washington, D.C. metropolitan areas, respectively. For the
three month period ended March 31, 2005, the average
economic occupancy rate, defined as gross potential rent less
vacancy losses, model expenses and bad debt expenses divided by
gross potential rent for the period, of all of our stabilized
(same store) communities was 93.5%. The average monthly rental
rate per apartment unit at these communities for the three month
period ended March 31, 2005 was $1,043.

      
Our business strategy is to deliver superior satisfaction and
value to our residents, associates and investors, with a vision
to be the first choice in quality multifamily living. Key
elements of our business strategy are as follows:


Investment, Disposition and Acquisition Strategy

      
Our investment, disposition and acquisition strategy is to shape
and rebalance our real estate portfolio to achieve uniformly
high quality, low average age properties and cash flow
diversification. We plan to achieve our objectives by reducing
our asset concentration in Atlanta, Georgia and Dallas, Texas,
while at the same time, building critical mass in other core
markets where we may currently lack the portfolio size to
achieve operating efficiencies and the full value of the
Post® brand. We define critical mass for this purpose as at
least 2,000 apartment units or $200 million of investment
in a particular market. Our goal ultimately is to reduce our
concentration in Atlanta, Georgia, measured by dollars invested,
to not more than 30% of the portfolio.

      
We plan to achieve our objectives by selling our oldest and
least competitively located properties, and we may also consider
selling joint venture interests in some of our core properties
or selectively converting some of these properties to for-sale
(condominium) housing. We expect that this strategy will provide
capital to reinvest in new communities in dynamic neighborhoods
and may also allow for leveraged returns through joint venture
structures that preserve Post® branded property and asset
management.

      
We are focusing on a limited number of major cities and have
substantially re-established our regional value creation
capabilities. We have added skilled personnel to more
effectively pursue acquisitions, development, dispositions and
select multifamily for-sale (condominium) opportunities that are
consistent with our market strategy. Our value creation
capabilities include regional value creation teams in Atlanta,
Georgia (focusing on the Southeast), Washington, DC (focusing on
that market and New York, New York) and Dallas, Texas (focusing
on the Southwest). We have reduced the number of markets where
we operate from thirteen to nine, and we may exit one or more
additional markets in the future if we do not believe we can
achieve critical mass within a reasonable period of time. We may
also consider entering new markets in the future.

S-1



Table of Contents
      
Key elements of our investment and acquisition strategy include
instilling a disciplined team approach to development and
acquisition decisions and selecting sites and properties in
infill suburban and urban locations in strong primary markets
that serve the higher-end multifamily consumer. We will focus
development on the product types that are more affordable to the
deepest segment of the upper end market in each city. We will,
therefore, look to develop more infill garden style communities
in our sunbelt markets and urban and mixed-use communities in
those markets and submarkets with existing density and barriers
to entry to warrant such communities. We plan to develop,
construct and continually maintain and improve our apartment
communities consistent with quality standards management
believes are synonymous with the Post® brand. New
acquisitions will be limited to properties that meet or that are
expected to be repositioned and improved to meet our quality and
location requirements. We will generally pursue acquisitions
either to rebalance our property portfolio, using the proceeds
of asset sales to redeploy capital in markets where critical
mass is desired, or to pursue opportunistic purchases on a
selective basis where market conditions warrant.


Post® Brand Name Strategy

      
The Post® brand name has been cultivated for more than
30 years, and its promotion has been integral to our
success. Management believes that the Post® brand name is
synonymous with quality upscale apartment communities that are
situated in desirable locations and that provide a high level of
resident service. We believe that we provide our residents with
a high level of service, including attractive landscaping and
numerous amenities, including controlled access, high-speed
internet connectivity, on-site business centers, on-site
courtesy officers, urban vegetable gardens and fitness centers
at a number of our communities.

      
Key elements in implementing our brand name strategy include
extensively utilizing the trademarked brand name and
coordinating our advertising programs to increase brand name
recognition. During 2004, we initiated a new marketing campaign,
initiated new customer service programs designed to raise
resident satisfaction and provided employees and residents new
opportunities for community involvement, all intended to enhance
what we believe is a valuable asset.

      
In early 2005, we announced the launch of a new for-sale housing
brand, Post Preferred
Homestm,
which will serve as the unified marketing umbrella for our
for-sale ventures, including developing new communities and
converting existing assets into upscale for-sale (condominium)
housing in several key markets. Our for-sale ventures will be
marketed under the Post Preferred
Homestm
brand to differentiate for-sale product from our rental
portfolio while capitalizing on our unique brand heritage.


Service and Associate Development Strategy

      
Our service orientation strategy includes utilizing independent
third parties to regularly measure resident satisfaction and
providing performance incentives to our associates linked to
delivering a high level of service and enhancing resident
satisfaction. We also plan to achieve our objective by investing
in the development and implementation of training programs
focused on associate development, improving the quality of our
operations and the delivery of resident service.


Operating Strategy

      
Our operating strategy includes striving to be an innovator and
a leader in anticipating customer needs while achieving
operating consistency across our properties. We also will
continue to explore opportunities to improve processes and
technology that drive efficiency in our business. In 2005, we
intend to implement new property operating and centralized
procurement software for this purpose.


Financing Strategy

      
Our financing strategy is to maintain a strong balance sheet and
to maintain our investment grade credit rating. We plan to
achieve our objectives by generally maintaining total effective
leverage (debt and preferred equity) as a percentage of
undepreciated real estate assets in a range of 50% to 55%, by
generally limiting variable rate indebtedness as a percentage of
total indebtedness to not more than 20% to 25% of aggregate

S-2



Table of Contents

indebtedness, and by maintaining adequate liquidity through our
unsecured lines of credit. We used borrowings available under
our revolving credit facilities to pay off $125 million of
our unsecured notes, including our 6.85% Mandatory Par Put
Remarketed Securities on March 16, 2005, which caused our
variable rate indebtedness as a percentage of total indebtedness
to exceed 25% as of March 31, 2005. However, on an as
adjusted basis after giving effect to this offering and the
application of the proceeds therefrom, as of March 31,
2005, our total variable rate indebtedness as a percentage of
total indebtedness would have been below 20%. At March 31,
2005, our total effective leverage (debt and preferred equity)
as a percentage of undepreciated real estate assets was below
50%.

      
Post Properties is a self-administered and self-managed equity
real estate investment trust, or REIT. Through its wholly owned
subsidiaries, Post Properties is the sole general partner of
Post Apartment Homes and it held 94.3% of the common units in
Post Apartment Homes as of March 31, 2005. Post Properties
conducts all of its business through Post Apartment Homes and
subsidiaries of Post Apartment Homes.

      
Our executive offices are located at One Riverside,
4401 Northside Parkway, Suite 800, Atlanta, Georgia
30327 and our telephone number is (404) 846-5000.






USE OF PROCEEDS

      
The net proceeds to Post Apartment Homes from this offering,
after payment of the underwriting discount and all expenses of
the offering, are expected to be approximately
$99.0 million. We intend to use the net proceeds from this
offering to reduce amounts outstanding under our revolving
credit facilities and for general corporate purposes. At
March 31, 2005, our revolving credit facilities had an
aggregate outstanding balance of $208.6 million and bore
interest at an average rate of 3.46%. The revolving credit
facilities will mature in January 2007. Affiliates of Wachovia
Capital Markets, LLC, PNC Capital Markets, Inc., SunTrust
Capital Markets, Inc. and Wells Fargo Securities, LLC are
lenders under our revolving credit facilities and will,
therefore, receive a portion of the proceeds from the sale of
the notes in this offering.

